        {"q": "Mengapa composition sering dipilih dibanding inheritance?", "options": ["Selalu memakai memori lebih sedikit", "Membuat perilaku lebih fleksibel dari komponen kecil", "Menghapus kebutuhan protocol", "Hanya bekerja pada struct"], "answer": "Membuat perilaku lebih fleksibel dari komponen kecil", "explanation": "Composition menyusun kemampuan dari objek atau komponen kecil sehingga dependensi lebih longgar dan perilaku lebih mudah diganti atau diuji.",
         "q_en": "Why is composition often preferred over inheritance?", "options_en": ["Always uses less memory", "Makes behavior more flexible from smaller components", "Removes the need for protocols", "Only works on structs"], "answer_en": "Makes behavior more flexible from smaller components", "explanation_en": "Composition assembles capabilities from smaller objects or components, resulting in looser dependencies and behavior that is easier to swap or test."},
        {"q": "Apa fungsi protocol conformance?", "options": ["Menjamin tipe memenuhi requirement protocol", "Mengubah class menjadi struct", "Membuat semua property public", "Mencegah instance dibuat"], "answer": "Menjamin tipe memenuhi requirement protocol", "explanation": "Tipe yang conform pada protocol wajib menyediakan requirement yang ditentukan, sehingga dapat digunakan melalui interface protocol yang sama.",
         "q_en": "What is the purpose of protocol conformance?", "options_en": ["Guarantee a type satisfies the protocol's requirements", "Convert a class to a struct", "Make all properties public", "Prevent instances from being created"], "answer_en": "Guarantee a type satisfies the protocol's requirements", "explanation_en": "A type that conforms to a protocol must provide the specified requirements, allowing it to be used through the same protocol interface."},
        {"q": "Pada reference type, perubahan melalui satu variabel dapat terlihat pada variabel lain karena...", "options": ["Nilai selalu disalin", "Keduanya dapat menunjuk instance yang sama", "Compiler menghapus objek lama", "Semua property menjadi static"], "answer": "Keduanya dapat menunjuk instance yang sama", "explanation": "Class adalah reference type. Beberapa variabel dapat menyimpan referensi ke instance yang sama, sehingga mutasi terlihat dari seluruh referensi tersebut.",
         "q_en": "With a reference type, a change through one variable is visible via another variable because...", "options_en": ["Values are always copied", "Both can point to the same instance", "The compiler deletes the old object", "All properties become static"], "answer_en": "Both can point to the same instance", "explanation_en": "A class is a reference type. Multiple variables can store a reference to the same instance, so mutations are visible through all those references."},
